<item>
            <title>[AMQ-5404] LevelDB files not being released after deletion</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-5404</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;During numerous test runs we&apos;ve seen the file system fill up (df -k) and eventually ActiveMQ failing with a short write error.  When ActiveMQ falls over the file system is freed up to its original state. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Before ActiveMQ falls over we&apos;ve tried to find the reason for the file system filling up by hunting through the directories but to no avail.  However when we do a lsof -a +L1 we can see numerous deleted LevelDB log and index files.   &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Does anybody know why ActiveMQ/LevelDB is not releasing these files for full clear up by the OS. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is on &lt;br/&gt;
Red Hat Linux 6.4 &lt;br/&gt;
ActiveMQ 5.10 &lt;br/&gt;
Java 1.7.0_45 &lt;/p&gt;</description>
